    <!-- Use the following table cell for all of your page data --> 
     
    <td width="515" align="left"> 
      <p> The standard footer for university pages can be mirrored from the url: 
        <a href="http://www.unimelb.edu.au/include/footer/footer.htm">http://www.unimelb.edu.au/include/footer/footer.htm 
        </a></p>
      <p>Please ensure that the mirrored information is updated regularly &#151; 
        at least once a week.</p>
      <h3>UNIX Servers</h3>
      <p>Unix administrators can use the wget program, available from: <a href="http://sunsite.auc.dk/ftp/pub/infosystems/wget/">http://sunsite.auc.dk/ftp/pub/infosystems/wget/</a> 
        and run it once per day via cron: 30 4 * * * /path/to/wget </p>
      <h3>Windows Servers</h3>
      <p>Windows Servers can also use wget. </p>
      <h3>Macintosh Servers</h3>
      <p>Mac Server administrators can use the Mirror program, available from: 
        <a href="http://filedudes.ionsys.com/mac/ftp/mirror.html">http://filedudes.ionsys.com/mac/ftp/mirror.html</a> 
        (free for non-commercial use) and copy the footer from: <a href="ftp://www.unimelb.edu.au/unimelb-only/include/footer/footer.htm">ftp://www.unimelb.edu.au/unimelb-only/include/footer/footer.htm</a> 
        A free Macintosh cron system is also available from: <a href="http://soli.inav.net/%7Edoshel/daemon.html%20">http://soli.inav.net/~doshel/daemon.html 
        </a> </p>
      <h3>Server-Side Includes</h3>
      <p>Server administrators also need to enable server-side includes. Unix 
        servers should be using the apache web server (<a href="http://www.apache.org/">http://www.apache.org/</a>), 
        and can do so by adding the following line to their srm.conf file: AddHandler 
        server-parsed .html <br>
        and changing the 'Options' line for the DocumentRoot in the access.conf 
        file so that includes are allowed: Options [other options] +Includes</p>
      Maintainers of other servers should refer to their server 
      documentation for information on how to enable server-side includes. </td>
  </tr>
</table>


